<subSubSection id="28FB2ABD967BCB29D3C17E6DFDCA9BF7" pageId="0" pageNumber="191" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="03B2621DB8C8BCE8D68BC989F49E87AF" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">
<taxonomicName id="0E947C5119CCF767C8735102080E0BF5" LSID="16173DC4-7FFA-5F66-A2AD-F4FE6A732C59" authority="Toll, 1961" authorityName="Toll" authorityYear="1961" class="Insecta" family="Coleophoridae" genus="Coleophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Coleophora impalella" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impalella">Coleophora impalella Toll, 1961</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AD6E3D9DAA43A9E7F8E2DCB788CA96CC" pageId="0" pageNumber="191" type="case and behaviour">
<paragraph id="013A5B01BFBBFF24C101F25199244473" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">Case and behaviour.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="75C3F8EC65D63505C3CDF84D38C2E877" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">
Construction of the case begins in late August or early September from the leaves of the host plant, 
<taxonomicName id="1A811B632EDE321B94152328066E0EB8" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Galatella" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Galatella sedifolia" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="191" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sedifolia">
<emphasis id="7BA188AFDDD6CE2AFA6125A00B093B4A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">Galatella sedifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This finding does not support 
<bibRefCitation id="BBD67B407C81B05645DF622B8CA6F3E2" author="Richter, I" journalOrPublisher="hu" pageId="0" pageNumber="191" publicationUrl="http://www.coleophoridae.bluefile.cz/?p=2854" refId="B26" refString="Richter, I, 2021. Coleophora impalella Toll, 1961. http://www.coleophoridae.bluefile.cz/?p=2854" title="Coleophora impalella Toll, 1961." url="http://www.coleophoridae.bluefile.cz/?p=2854" year="2021">Richter (2021)</bibRefCitation>
, who has found cases on 
<emphasis id="7926D43F0B176CD374C867822481765B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">G. linosyris</emphasis>
(L.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="87DF5C5A29C12AF703DE2CA0AACFEA81" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">
The case is made of 2-6 mm long and 2-4 mm wide strips spun to each other with overlap, resulting in a sheath case (Figs 
<figureCitation id="49999095C72722F14241C52B57E64876" captionStart="Figures 24–27" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figures 24 - 27. Some stages and habitat of C. impalella. 24. L 5 case of C. impalella before overwintering, Belmegyer, 13. x. 2020; 25. L 4 case of C. impalella before overwintering, Belmegyer 24. ix. 2020; 26. Imago of C. impalella from Szabadkigyos, Kigyosi puszta, 12. v. 2021; 27. Habitat of C. impalella in Szabadkigyos, Kigyosi puszta, 20. v. 2021. Scale bar: 3 mm (24); 2 mm (25); 2.1 mm (26). Figs 24, 26: photo by A. Takacs, Figs 25, 27: photo by G. Boldog." figureDoi="10.3897/nl.45.80106.figures24-27" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/675399" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">24</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="DFC7A3AFFBEC506F0880E3B28F98C5B0" captionStart="Figures 24–27" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figures 24 - 27. Some stages and habitat of C. impalella. 24. L 5 case of C. impalella before overwintering, Belmegyer, 13. x. 2020; 25. L 4 case of C. impalella before overwintering, Belmegyer 24. ix. 2020; 26. Imago of C. impalella from Szabadkigyos, Kigyosi puszta, 12. v. 2021; 27. Habitat of C. impalella in Szabadkigyos, Kigyosi puszta, 20. v. 2021. Scale bar: 3 mm (24); 2 mm (25); 2.1 mm (26). Figs 24, 26: photo by A. Takacs, Figs 25, 27: photo by G. Boldog." figureDoi="10.3897/nl.45.80106.figures24-27" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/675399" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">25</figureCitation>
). Feeding lasts until drying of host plant in autumn. The overwintering case is 12 mm long and is attached to a broader section of the dried plant. The larva continues feeding on fresh leaves in spring. Early case is greyish black, changing to dark brown after overwintering. Mouth directed in 40 ° angle to longitudinal axis of case, case slightly tapering towards anal end, caudal 2/3 part slightly curved, anal end flattened, bivalved.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0FCD00BF2ABA4FB86E1EFCFF36500429" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">Adults emerge 10-12 days after the permanent attachment of the case. They fly in daytime and remain close to the host plant. Mating was observed between 11 h and 13 h.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2D9213C782911EA29A11522EDB50689C" pageId="0" pageNumber="191" type="l5 larva">
<paragraph id="5C9C9BD76EC12611AD6B75F657AD4E34" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">L5 larva</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A804D5B0CA340E0DBBA860932FBD7F2C" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis id="69DE0111FDDF639600414D323AF9F35C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">
(Figs 
<figureCitation id="3AE61E1A8C8604BB058C6AD4D49756A9" captionStart="Figures 18–23" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 18 - 23. Larval morphology of Coleophora impalella. 18. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 19. Head and thorax, lateral view; 20. Head and thorax, ventral view; 21. Prolegs on segments A 3 - A 6, ventral view; 22. Anal prolegs, ventral view; 23. Anal plate, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1 mm, cranial direction top, caudal direction bottom, photos by A. Takacs." figureDoi="10.3897/nl.45.80106.figures18-23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/675398" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">18-23</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Length 5.5 mm. Head brown, adfrontal suture black. Body light brown, with inconspicuous pinacula around prolegs on segments A3-A5. Thoracic shields shiny black, rounded; prothoracic shield ovoid, more than 1.5 times as broad as long, very finely divided along median axis except anterior margin; mesothoracic shield D-shaped, divided to two halves by gap medially, gap being narrowest at middle, shield gradually broadening towards anterior and posterior margins, anterior margin straight, lighter than rest of the shield; metathoracic shield made of two separated ovoid plates with dentate inner edges, plates separated by gap slightly broader than the plates (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2B73436DF0349CAF3D0AE2011D6742D7" captionStart="Figures 18–23" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 18 - 23. Larval morphology of Coleophora impalella. 18. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 19. Head and thorax, lateral view; 20. Head and thorax, ventral view; 21. Prolegs on segments A 3 - A 6, ventral view; 22. Anal prolegs, ventral view; 23. Anal plate, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1 mm, cranial direction top, caudal direction bottom, photos by A. Takacs." figureDoi="10.3897/nl.45.80106.figures18-23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/675398" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">18</figureCitation>
). Spiracular sclerites oval, of equal length, sclerite on prothorax half as broad as those on meso- and metathorax, latter two sclerites with uniform shape and size (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="571C98F017FE36CE9D9BCFD0A59D6934" captionStart="Figures 18–23" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 18 - 23. Larval morphology of Coleophora impalella. 18. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 19. Head and thorax, lateral view; 20. Head and thorax, ventral view; 21. Prolegs on segments A 3 - A 6, ventral view; 22. Anal prolegs, ventral view; 23. Anal plate, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1 mm, cranial direction top, caudal direction bottom, photos by A. Takacs." figureDoi="10.3897/nl.45.80106.figures18-23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/675398" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">19</figureCitation>
). Thoracic legs brown; proximal parts of segments darker than distal parts (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FC8FD66B470714CF384E9E0C2BAD2213" captionStart="Figures 18–23" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 18 - 23. Larval morphology of Coleophora impalella. 18. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 19. Head and thorax, lateral view; 20. Head and thorax, ventral view; 21. Prolegs on segments A 3 - A 6, ventral view; 22. Anal prolegs, ventral view; 23. Anal plate, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1 mm, cranial direction top, caudal direction bottom, photos by A. Takacs." figureDoi="10.3897/nl.45.80106.figures18-23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/675398" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">20</figureCitation>
). Prolegs on segments A3-A5 with 6-6 crochets in two uniordinal rows; on segment A5 two crochets in anterior, four crochets in posterior row, three crochets in each of remaining row (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2370205A8FD381A458B78F82FB55F918" captionStart="Figures 18–23" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 18 - 23. Larval morphology of Coleophora impalella. 18. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 19. Head and thorax, lateral view; 20. Head and thorax, ventral view; 21. Prolegs on segments A 3 - A 6, ventral view; 22. Anal prolegs, ventral view; 23. Anal plate, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1 mm, cranial direction top, caudal direction bottom, photos by A. Takacs." figureDoi="10.3897/nl.45.80106.figures18-23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/675398" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">21</figureCitation>
). Anal plate matt black, heavily irrorated with tiny hollows (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="825540A8A9564FB8B2016EC1DE76D6C9" captionStart="Figures 18–23" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 18 - 23. Larval morphology of Coleophora impalella. 18. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 19. Head and thorax, lateral view; 20. Head and thorax, ventral view; 21. Prolegs on segments A 3 - A 6, ventral view; 22. Anal prolegs, ventral view; 23. Anal plate, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1 mm, cranial direction top, caudal direction bottom, photos by A. Takacs." figureDoi="10.3897/nl.45.80106.figures18-23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/675398" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">23</figureCitation>
). Anal proleg half-moon-shaped, each with 17-19 crochets (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C72F843B65600E8A4E340CDB7F6D58E4" captionStart="Figures 18–23" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 18 - 23. Larval morphology of Coleophora impalella. 18. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 19. Head and thorax, lateral view; 20. Head and thorax, ventral view; 21. Prolegs on segments A 3 - A 6, ventral view; 22. Anal prolegs, ventral view; 23. Anal plate, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1 mm, cranial direction top, caudal direction bottom, photos by A. Takacs." figureDoi="10.3897/nl.45.80106.figures18-23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/675398" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">22</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
