<paragraph id="59D56948E2851CB18B2133CC45BB75B9" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">
In addition to the Hungarian locality already known, the species was also found in 
<normalizedToken id="DA3D974166FB2A01F95404BF00C19269" originalValue="Szabadkígyós">Szabadkigyos</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="7F39018C0B4D85DC7730E123058EBB6D" originalValue="Kígyósi">Kigyosi</normalizedToken>
puszta on 12.v.2021 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C9607479E99C94BFF99D81A59F4187F6" captionStart="Figures 24–27" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figures 24 - 27. Some stages and habitat of C. impalella. 24. L 5 case of C. impalella before overwintering, Belmegyer, 13. x. 2020; 25. L 4 case of C. impalella before overwintering, Belmegyer 24. ix. 2020; 26. Imago of C. impalella from Szabadkigyos, Kigyosi puszta, 12. v. 2021; 27. Habitat of C. impalella in Szabadkigyos, Kigyosi puszta, 20. v. 2021. Scale bar: 3 mm (24); 2 mm (25); 2.1 mm (26). Figs 24, 26: photo by A. Takacs, Figs 25, 27: photo by G. Boldog." figureDoi="10.3897/nl.45.80106.figures24-27" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/675399" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">26</figureCitation>
). One case was collected in Elek on 06.x.2021 and one case in 
<normalizedToken id="FC1DB8995B6175C74E435B68927C6095" originalValue="Grăniceri">Grăniceri</normalizedToken>
, Romania on 06.x.2021. This latter record is the first one outside Russia and Hungary. New to Romania.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D5D7ED330E03833866F51EA1B1F42EBF" pageId="0" pageNumber="191" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="898A0E36B7ACFA0952B0676CF62CDB86" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FC8D9898A6D8FA62AAE2E8A664BE6281" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">
<taxonomicName id="608E921A4B53D3D2A997A2296DD282DB" authorityName="Toll" authorityYear="1961" class="Insecta" family="Coleophoridae" genus="Coleophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Coleophora impalella" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impalella">
<emphasis id="77184CCEA98F60EB2D4596A40E786190" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">Coleophora impalella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
feeds on 
<taxonomicName id="65E18B187A3A3043AE521FBF82530297" genus="Asteretum" lsidName="Asteretum sedifolii" pageId="0" pageNumber="191" rank="species" species="sedifolii">
<emphasis id="65311C91BF47C644A376F5E74297D5E3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">Asteretum sedifolii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="3C6BF397F6DD485EAF0068E473AC5FD5" originalValue="Soó">Soo</normalizedToken>
1947 corr. Borhidi 1996 (Pannonic salt steppes and salt marshes), a species that is highly influenced by dry continental climate with extreme temperatures and uneven distribution of precipitation. This habitat type was formed by secondary salinisation (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DE0CCCE291F743713FF2E549FFEEBAFB" captionStart="Figures 24–27" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figures 24 - 27. Some stages and habitat of C. impalella. 24. L 5 case of C. impalella before overwintering, Belmegyer, 13. x. 2020; 25. L 4 case of C. impalella before overwintering, Belmegyer 24. ix. 2020; 26. Imago of C. impalella from Szabadkigyos, Kigyosi puszta, 12. v. 2021; 27. Habitat of C. impalella in Szabadkigyos, Kigyosi puszta, 20. v. 2021. Scale bar: 3 mm (24); 2 mm (25); 2.1 mm (26). Figs 24, 26: photo by A. Takacs, Figs 25, 27: photo by G. Boldog." figureDoi="10.3897/nl.45.80106.figures24-27" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/675399" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">27</figureCitation>
). It is characteristic for the Continental climate zone and can also be found in the Ukrainian and Russian steppe belt (
<bibRefCitation id="4A3751E5325A3953DDD9FDDFE2D811DC" author="Borhidi, A" journalOrPublisher="Akademiai Kiado, Budapest" pageId="0" pageNumber="191" refId="B14" refString="Borhidi, A, 2003. Magyarorszag noevenytarsulasai. Akademiai Kiado, Budapest" title="Magyarorszag noevenytarsulasai." year="2003">Borhidi 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="932DE615C0564DEE4FF2B5E64D7F049F" pageId="0" pageNumber="191" type="parasitoids">
<paragraph id="7AB4694E18717358A58B0121B9B1439A" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">Parasitoids.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B10A5B687BF89F687F4DE20D6A813542" pageId="0" pageNumber="191">
